README.uemacs

This is my personal variety of microemacs, ported and nursed along since
the 90's. It is descended from MicroEMACS 5.03, written by Jean-Pierre
Demailly which was based on MicroEMACS 3.12 written by Daniel M. Lawrence
based on code by Dave G. Conroy.

My fingers know what to do and old habits die hard.

It does not depend on anything except libc. (I added an internal termcap
library based on GNU termcap 1.3.1 in order to remove that dependency since
Linux distros stopped shipping termcap. FWIW IMHO termcap is about a
million times more sensible than terminfo.)

I have removed a ton of ancient, obsolete and not supportable by me code
related to long dead operating systems. Ok, I also gutted the MSDOS and
Windows NT support. And the various non-GCC compilers. I have trimmed it
down to remove as much conditional compilation as I could.

There are some "quirks"...

1) It will core dump if your terminal has too many lines. The trigger
number seems to vary but is usually around 128+ I have no idea why. My
efforts to find the root of that problem have all failed.

2) The current code is very specific to Linux. It has not been built on any
other platform for a long time.

3) I would love to adapt it to Mac OS but I have not found the time. I did
mess around a bit and the needed changes don't seem large.

UPDATE: my good friend Claude brought everything up to POSIX and then we
did a few rounds of debugging and compiler message cleanup. Mac OS is now
supported!

4) The termcap file has been pared down to basically just xterm. Nobody
uses anything else but I probably still have old termcaps laying around if
you would like to dispute that contention.

5) The binary is shipped with ProTop as "uemacs" but I usually rename it to
"emacs". If you have and want real emacs you might want to keep the name as
"uemacs".

6) If you would like the C source just ask.  I will be happy to share.


To install this on Linux:

	sudo cp bin/uemacs  /usr/local/bin/emacs
	sudo cp etc/termcap /usr/local/etc
	sudo cp etc/emacsrc /usr/local/.emacsrc	# my personal key bindings

Add to .bash_profile:

	export TERMCAP=/usr/local/etc/termcap

or, if you would rather:

	sudo cp etc/termcap /usr/local/etc


